<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-10-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-10-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="791" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d791">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hardy</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-10-24"><hi rend="italic">October 24,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 32, Greek Series.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 59, of the 3d instant, relative
                            to the case of Mr. Economopoulos, a native of Greece naturalized in the
                            United States, who has been compelled to do military service in his
                            native country, has been received.</p>
                        <p>It is the opinion of the Department, under the circumstances set forth in
                            your dispatch, that you have done all that you could properly do in Mr.
                            Economopoulos’ behalf.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>